{"id": "duc04-testb-33:0#1", "contents": "Many Arabs recall Sharon's involvement in the 1982 invasion of Lebanon, where an Israeli tribunal found him indirectly responsible for the massacre of hundreds of Palestinian refugees by Christian Lebanese militiamen at two Beirut camps. This dark history has led the Syrian newspaper, Tishrin, to declare that Sharon's appointment is a ``bullet of mercy'' to the peace process, implying that it will likely bring about its demise."}
